result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
1:25 am - DA calls cases 16CM106, 16CM107 and 16CM116 and states appearances and agreement reached.  Defendant Karen Marie Dipalma appeared with attorney James Richard Lex.  Mark T. Fuhr appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  DE enters plea of NO CONTEST to 16CM106 and Ct 1 in 16CM116.  Court questions DE regarding the plea.  DA explains elements of charge.  Court finds plea/waiver to be free, etc.  Court finds factual basis does exist.  Court accepts plea, finds DE guilty and orders entry of JOC on 16CM106, and defers entry of JOC on Ct 1 of 16CM116, and on motion of DA, dismisses Ct 2 on 16CM116, and dismisses but reads in 16CM107 for purposes of collecting service fees and blood draw cost.  DA certifies victims rights compliance.  DE to submit DNA sample at PRSO.  Court imposes:

16CM106  Sentence withheld - 1 year probation
Conditions of probation
$300 fine
$200 DNAAS
$130 SBDA
$65.50 blood draw cost to County
DE must maintain absolute sobriety.

16CM116  Deferred order for 1 year
See written order. DA to redraft to include $100 DOMAB

Appeal rights given
Plea/sentencing hearing on April 18, 2017 at 11:00 am.

If not already completed DE must submit to booking at Sheriff's Dept prior to release.
Defendant shall give written notice prior to any change in address or telephone number to the Clerk of this Court and Defense Attorney.  DE shall not consume any alcohol.

Cases 16CM106 and 16CM107.  Defendant Karen Marie Dipalma appeared with attorney James Richard Lex.  Mark T. Fuhr appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Complaint acknowledged, reading waived.  DE enters plea of NOT GUILTY to all counts.  Court orders Pre-trial conference be scheduled.  One bond for both cases.
